@startuml C4_Browsing_Domain

title C4 - Modello di dominio Browsing

top to bottom direction
skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam classFontStyle bold
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam linetype ortho

package "Domain" {
  enum IntegrityStatusEnum {
    VALID
    INVALID
    UNKNOWN
  }

  enum MetadataType {
    STRING
    NUMBER
    BOOLEAN
    COMPOSITE
  }

  class Dip <<entity>> {
    +id: number | null
    +uuid: string
    +integrityStatus: IntegrityStatusEnum
  }

  class DocumentClass <<entity>> {
    +id: number | null
    +dipId: number | null
    +dipUuid: string
    +uuid: string
    +name: string
    +timestamp: string
    +integrityStatus: IntegrityStatusEnum
  }

  class Process <<entity>> {
    +id: number | null
    +documentClassId: number | null
    +documentClassUuid: string
    +uuid: string
    +metadata: Metadata
    +integrityStatus: IntegrityStatusEnum
  }

  class Document <<entity>> {
    +id: number | null
    +processId: number | null
    +processUuid: string
    +uuid: string
    +metadata: Metadata
    +integrityStatus: IntegrityStatusEnum
  }

  class File <<entity>> {
    +id: number | null
    +documentId: number | null
    +documentUuid: string
    +uuid: string
    +filename: string
    +path: string
    +hash: string
    +isMain: boolean
    +integrityStatus: IntegrityStatusEnum
  }

  class Metadata <<value-object>> {
    +name: string
    +type: MetadataType
    +value: string | Metadata[]
  }
}

note top of Dip
Gerarchia usata dai casi d'uso di browsing:
Dip -> DocumentClass -> Process -> Document -> File
end note

note bottom of File
Questo diagramma rappresenta le entity di dominio in core/src/entity.
Le entity non sono aggregate tra loro: mantengono solo
riferimenti al padre (id/uuid) usati nei flussi di dominio
e nel mapping di persistenza.
end note

@enduml
